.TH "kthread_freezable_should_stop" 9 "kthread_freezable_should_stop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kthread_freezable_should_stop \- should this freezable kthread return now?
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" kthread_freezable_should_stop
.BI "(bool *was_frozen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "was_frozen" 12
optional out parameter, indicates whether current was frozen
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBkthread_should_stop\fP for freezable kthreads, which will enter
refrigerator if necessary.  This function is safe from \fBkthread_stop\fP /
freezer deadlock and freezable kthreads should use this function instead
of calling \fBtry_to_freeze\fP directly.
